channel.title: Run error DeathlyPVPz
channel.description: I tried use my run.bat it was working fine and then I closed it and tried re-opening it and it gave me some error I know for you all out there it must be easy, So I would really appreciate it if anyone could help me in anyway. I have been away from rsps due to my mid term for a while so pretty much lost it all haha. Anyways here's a screenshot: http://prntscr.com/28s79p Please let me know what it is. Thanks! Much appareciated!

item.title: Run error DeathlyPVPz
item.dc:creator: @malimt malimt
item.description:
@malimt wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:9, topic:536488”][quote author=malimt link=topic=655302.msg4387784#msg4387784 date=1386304828]

This “error” is basically saying that there isn’t enough allotted memory for the Java Virtual Machine to run. I do not know how to fix it however, google it.

Are you serious?
You just change the -Xmx argument to a higher number…

Would you mind giving me a number to change it to? I tried changing to 2000, 3000, and 4000 didnt work it was already on 1300

EDIT: You we’re wrong it actually had to come lower. Now it’s working prefectly fine. But appreciate for trying to help guys.
[/quote]
I never saw the error. So I only half guessed based on what he said.[/quote] Np. thanks anyways.
